nt CYP450 3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/41276/', '', 'Lamivudine, Paritaprevir, Glecaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Maraviroc, Simeprevir, Cabotegravir, Valaciclovir, Zanamivir, Lenacapavir, Velpatasvir, More', 'Fluorometholone, Indomethacin, Fluocinolone acetonide, Diclofenac, Tetracycline, Acetylsalicylic acid, Minocycline, Amphotericin B, Doxycycline, Epinephrine, Chlorhexidine, More', 1767369485);
